The parents of a KDF soldier killed in the Friday Kulbiyow attack in Somalia went to Nairobi on Sunday to view and collect the body of their son.Gideon Nyabidi comes from Kesogon village in Kwanza, Trans Nzoia. He was last home in December.Relative Milcah Sugut said this is a second tragedy for the family as Nyabidi&rsquo;s mother Esther Chemeli (pictured) was involved in an accident in November and is now paralysed.Nyabidi is survived by his widow Loyce Nyabidi and his three-month-old son.Al Shabaab said it killed at least 57 Kenyan soldiers, a claim KDF denies.